sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>Authentication
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NBController as Notebook Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant KServe as KServe Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant ModelCtl as ODH Model Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Istio as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Predictor as Predictor Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Predictor: Workflow: Model Training to Deployment

    User->>OAuth: Login to OpenShift
    OAuth-->>User: Bearer Token (JWT)

    User->>Dashboard: Access dashboard<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Dashboard->>Dashboard: Validate token via SAR
    Dashboard-->>User: Project management UI

    User->>Dashboard: Create data science project
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create namespace + RBAC

    User->>Dashboard: Launch Jupyter notebook
    Dashboard->>NBController: Create Notebook CR
    NBController->>NBController: Inject OAuth proxy sidecar
    NBController->>Notebook: Spawn StatefulSet
    NBController->>Router: Create OpenShift Route<br/>TLS Edge termination
    Router-->>User: Notebook URL (HTTPS)

    User->>Router: Access notebook<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    Router->>Notebook: Forward to OAuth proxy<br/>8443/TCP
    Notebook->>OAuth: Validate token
    OAuth-->>Notebook: Token valid
    Notebook-->>User: JupyterLab interface

    User->>Notebook: Train ML model
    Notebook->>Notebook: Execute training code
    Notebook->>S3: Upload trained model<br/>HTTPS, AWS IAM Auth
    S3-->>Notebook: Model saved

    User->>Dashboard: Deploy model (InferenceService)
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>storageUri: s3://bucket/model

    KServe->>KServe: Validate InferenceService
    KServe->>Predictor: Create Knative Service or Deployment

    ModelCtl->>KServe: Watch InferenceService CR
    ModelCtl->>Router: Create OpenShift Route<br/>TLS Passthrough
    ModelCtl->>Istio: Create PeerAuthentication<br/>mTLS STRICT
    ModelCtl->>ModelCtl: Create NetworkPolicies (3x)
    ModelCtl->>Istio: Add namespace to ServiceMeshMemberRoll

    Predictor->>Predictor: storage-initializer init container
    Predictor->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    S3-->>Predictor: Model artifacts

    Predictor->>Predictor: Load model into memory
    Predictor->>Predictor: Ready for inference

    Note over User,Predictor: Inference Request Flow

    User->>Router: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Body: inference payload
    Router->>Istio: Forward via VirtualService<br/>TLS Passthrough
    Istio->>Predictor: mTLS (STRICT)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    Predictor->>Predictor: Execute inference
    Predictor-->>Istio: Prediction result (JSON)
    Istio-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS response<br/>200 OK
